Q: Jim filled his dog's bowl with dog food. Starting at 8:00 am, Jim's dog ate exactly once an hour, consuming exactly 1/3 of the dog food remaining in the bowl at each feeding session. Approximately, what percent of the original food was in the dog's bowl right before the dog began to eat at noon of the same day?
Options: (a) 20% (b) 25% (c) 30% (d) 35% (e) 40%
A:
 Let the amount of dog food in the bowl at 8:00 am be 100. At 9:00 am, the amount of dog food in the bowl will be 100 - 1/3*100 = 67. At 10:00 am, the amount of dog food in the bowl will be 67 - 1/3*67 = 44.33. At 11:00 am, the amount of dog food in the bowl will be 44.33 - 1/3*44.33 = 29.89. At 12:00 pm, the amount of dog food in the bowl will be 29.89 - 1/3*29.89 = 19.96. So the answer is (d).

