Q: The price of a product is reduced by 30%. By what percentage should it be increased to make it 100%
Options: (a) 41.86% (b) 42.86% (c) 43.86% (d) 44.86% (e) 45.86%
A:
 Let the price be 100. It is reduced by 30% to 70. Now, 70 is increased by x% to make it 100. 70*(1+x/100) = 100 70 + 70*x/100 = 100 70*x/100 = 30 x = 30*100/70 = 42.86%. So the answer is (b).

