Q: there are more than 501 students in a school such that 20% of them exactly took physics and 28% of them exactly took math. What could be the least possible no of students in the school?
Options: (a) 550 (b) 570 (c) 600 (d) 700 (e) none of these
A:
 20% of them exactly took physics means 20% of the students took physics and no other subject. 28% of them exactly took math means 28% of the students took math and no other subject. So 20% of the students took physics and 28% of the students took math. So 20% + 28% = 48% of the students took either physics or math. So 52% of the students took neither physics nor math. So the least possible no of students in the school is 501*100/52 = 962. So the answer is (e).

