Q: Everyone in the family earns money each month. If the total income of a family per month is $9000 and the median income is $3000, how many members are there in the family?
Options: (a) 2 (b) 3 (c) 4 (d) 5 (e) 6
A:
 The median is the middle value. If there are 2 members, the median is the average of the two values. If there are 3 members, the median is the middle value. If there are 4 members, the median is the average of the two middle values. If there are 5 members, the median is the middle value. If there are 6 members, the median is the average of the two middle values. So the answer is (e).

