Q: A club consists of members whose ages are in A.P. The common difference being 3 months. If the youngest member of the club is just 7 years old and the sum of the ages of all the members is 250, then number of members in the club are :
Options: (a) 18 (b) 20 (c) 25 (d) 26 (e) 27
A:
 Let the number of members be n and the age of the youngest member be a. Then the age of the oldest member is a + (n-1)*3 = 250 - 7 = 243. So the sum of the ages of all the members is n/2(a + a + (n-1)*3) = 250. 2n(a + (n-1)*3)/2 = 250 2an + 3n(n-1) = 500 2a + 3n(n-1) = 250 2a + 3n^2 - 3n = 250 2a + 3n(n-1) = 250 2a + 3n^2 - 3n = 250 2a + 3n^2 - 3n - 250 = 0 3n^2 - 3n - 250 + 2a = 0 (n-10)(3n+25) = 0 n = 10 or n = -25/3. Since n is the number of members, it cannot be negative. So n = 10. So the answer is (b).

